│ An LLVM bug is causing a miscompilation due to an incorrect optimization of nested         │
│ `llvm.copysign` calls when the `nnan` (no NaNs) fast-math flag is present. The             │
│ transformation `copysign(x, copysign(y, z))` -> `copysign(x, z)` is generally valid, but   │
│ it becomes incorrect if the outer `copysign` has the `nnan` flag.                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ The issue arises because the inner `copysign(y, z)` can produce a non-NaN result even if   │
│ `z` is a NaN. When the optimization replaces the inner `copysign`'s result with `z` as the │
│ sign argument to the outer `copysign`, it exposes the outer call to a potential NaN. If    │
│ the outer call has the `nnan` flag, this leads to the result becoming `poison`, which is a │
│ miscompilation.                                                                            │
│                                                                                            │
│ To fix this, I will add a check to prevent this optimization when the outer `copysign`     │
│ instruction has the `nnan` flag. This ensures the transformation is only applied when it   │
│ is safe to do so.                                                                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will now apply this change to `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCalls.cpp`.    │
│                                                                                            │
│ <tool_call>                                                                                │
│ {                                                                                          │
│   "name": "edit",                                                                          │
│   "args": {                                                                                │
│     "file": "llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCalls.cpp",                        │
│     "old": "    if (match(Sign, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::copysign>(m_Value(),                │
│ m_Value(X))))\n      return replaceOperand(*II, 1, X);",                                   │
│     "new": "    if (match(Sign, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::copysign>(m_Value(), m_Value(X))))  │
│ {\n      // This is not valid if the outer copysign has nnan, because the inner\n      //  │
│ copysign might be hiding a NaN.\n      if (!II->hasNoNaNs())\n        return               │
│ replaceOperand(*II, 1, X);\n    }"                                                         │
│   }                                                                                        │
│ }                                                                                          │
│ </tool_call>                                                                               │
│ <tool_call>                                                                                │
